    "title": "Epoxy Floors for Classrooms, Cafeterias & Hallways - Elite Crete Systems",
    "content": "Classrooms, Cafeterias & Hallways\nThe two most commonly used flooring products specified for educational facilities are cost-effective vinyl (VCT) or expensive terrazzo. Our seamless resinous flooring systems compete with the lower cost associated with VCT while offering the high-end durability of terrazzo. These surfaces meet or exceed ADA Flat Surfaces, ADA Inclined Surfaces while also USDA, FDA and CFIA acceptable.\nAdvantages\nEasy to clean and maintain\nUltra-durable, high abrasion resistance withstands heavy traffic\nFluid applied systems for new construction or existing floor restoration\nFinish options include high gloss or satin\nVariable coefficient of friction (COF) levels to meet or exceed ADA Flat Surfaces, ADA Inclined Surfaces\nUSDA, FDA* and CFIA** acceptable.\nAntimicrobial and stain resistant\nSeamless flooring, no grout lines to harbor bacteria\n* Can be used in USDA facilities based on FSIS Directive 11,000.4 (Rev. 1), November 24, 1995.\n** Agriculture Canada (also known as Canadian Food Inspection Agency).\nPolymer Modified Cement\nPolymer Modified Cement\nClassrooms\nCafeterias\nHallways\nLabs\nLibraries\nOffices\nEntryways and common areas\nStairways\nPolymer Modified Cement\nREFLECTOR\nEnhancer\nREFLECTOR\nEnhancer HD\nUrethane Cement",
